  (
    'One-Arm Side Deadlift',
    'one-arm-side-deadlift',
    'legs',
    array['core', 'glutes', 'back']::text[],
    array['barbell']::text[],
    'hinge',
    'expert',
    'strength',
    true,
    array['Stand to the side of a barbell next to its center. Bend your knees and lower your body until you are able to reach the barbell.', 'Grasp the bar as if you were grabbing a briefcase (palms facing you since the bar is sideways). You may need a wrist wrap if you are using a significant amount of weight. This is your starting position.', 'Use your legs to help lift the barbell up while exhaling. Your arms should extend fully as bring the barbell up until you are in a standing position.', 'Slowly bring the barbell back down while inhaling. Tip: Make sure to bend your knees while lowering the weight to avoid any injury from occurring.', 'Repeat for the recommended amount of repetitions.', 'Switch arms and repeat the movement.']::text[],
    array['Using more weight or speed than you can control cleanly.', 'Skipping the setup and losing tension before the first rep starts.', 'Changing your body position between reps instead of keeping the movement repeatable.']::text[],
    array['Builds strength and control through the legs region.', 'Trains multiple joints at once, which can make your sessions more efficient.', 'Gives you a repeatable way to track progress inside Logbook over time.']::text[],
    array['Goblet Squat', 'Bodyweight Squat', 'Dumbbell Lunges']::text[],
    array['Romanian Deadlift', 'Barbell Squat', 'Front Barbell Squat']::text[],
    'One-Arm Side Deadlift Exercise: Muscles Worked, Tips, and How To Do It',
    'Learn how to do the One-Arm Side Deadlift exercise, which muscles it works, the equipment you need, and common mistakes to avoid.',
