  (
    'Bent-Arm Barbell Pullover',
    'bent-arm-barbell-pullover',
    'back',
    array['chest', 'shoulders', 'arms']::text[],
    array['barbell']::text[],
    'general',
    'intermediate',
    'strength',
    true,
    array['Lie on a flat bench with a barbell using a shoulder grip width.', 'Hold the bar straight over your chest with a bend in your arms. This will be your starting position.', 'While keeping your arms in the bent arm position, lower the weight slowly in an arc behind your head while breathing in until you feel a stretch on the chest.', 'At that point, bring the barbell back to the starting position using the arc through which the weight was lowered and exhale as you perform this movement.', 'Hold the weight on the initial position for a second and repeat the motion for the prescribed number of repetitions.']::text[],
    array['Using more weight or speed than you can control cleanly.', 'Cutting the range of motion short and rushing through the reps.', 'Changing your body position between reps instead of keeping the movement repeatable.']::text[],
    array['Builds strength and control through the back region.', 'Trains multiple joints at once, which can make your sessions more efficient.', 'Gives you a repeatable way to track progress inside Logbook over time.']::text[],
    array['Bodyweight Mid Row', 'Bent Over Two-Dumbbell Row', 'Wide-Grip Lat Pulldown']::text[],
    array['Bent Over Barbell Row', 'Barbell Shrug', 'Barbell Deadlift']::text[],
    'Bent-Arm Barbell Pullover Exercise: Muscles Worked, Tips, and How To Do It',
