  (
    'Clean Deadlift',
    'clean-deadlift',
    'legs',
    array['arms', 'glutes', 'back']::text[],
    array['barbell']::text[],
    'hinge',
    'beginner',
    'olympic-weightlifting',
    true,
    array['Begin standing with a barbell close to your shins. Your feet should be directly under your hips with your feet turned out slightly. Grip the bar with a double overhand grip or hook grip, about shoulder width apart. Squat down to the bar. Your spine should be in full extension, with a back angle that places your shoulders in front of the bar and your back as vertical as possible.', 'Begin by driving through the floor through the front of your heels. As the bar travels upward, maintain a constant back angle. Flare your knees out to the side to help keep them out of the bar''s path.', 'After the bar crosses the knees, complete the lift by driving the hips into the bar until your hips and knees are extended.']::text[],
    array['Using more weight or speed than you can control cleanly.', 'Skipping the setup and losing tension before the first rep starts.', 'Changing your body position between reps instead of keeping the movement repeatable.']::text[],
    array['Builds strength and control through the legs region.', 'Trains multiple joints at once, which can make your sessions more efficient.', 'Gives you a repeatable way to track progress inside Logbook over time.']::text[],
    array['Goblet Squat', 'Bodyweight Squat', 'Dumbbell Lunges']::text[],
